iris dataset¶

  • $N =150$ datapoints
  • $d = 4$ features: Sepal Length, Sepal Width, Petal Length and Petal Width

$\mathcal{D} = X \in \mathbb{R}^{150 \times 4}$

  • $c = 3$ classes: Setosa, Versicolour, and Virginica

Image('./img/iris-machinelearning.png')

typical workflow:

  • explore the data

https://scikit-learn.org/stable/auto_examples/datasets/plot_iris_dataset.html

  • find simple structure of the data

https://scikit-learn.org/stable/auto_examples/decomposition/plot_pca_iris.html

  • simple data analysis : classification (i)

https://scikit-learn.org/stable/auto_examples/tree/plot_iris.html

  • simple data analysis : classification (ii)

https://scikit-learn.org/stable/auto_examples/cluster/plot_cluster_iris.html

digits dataset¶

  • $N = 1797$ datapoitns
  • $d = 64$ features: $8 \times{} 8$ grayscale images

$D = X \in \{0, 255\}^{1797 \times 8 \times 8}$

  • $c = 10$ classes: $0,1,\ldots,9$
  • explore the data

https://scikit-learn.org/stable/auto_examples/datasets/plot_digits_last_image.html

  • simple data analysis

https://scikit-learn.org/stable/auto_examples/classification/plot_digits_classification.html

model comparison¶

  • zoo of methods

https://scikit-learn.org/stable/auto_examples/classification/plot_classifier_comparison.html

  • cross-validation

https://scikit-learn.org/stable/auto_examples/exercises/plot_cv_digits.html

pipelines¶

  • combining several methods
  • typical: feature extraction before classification

https://scikit-learn.org/stable/auto_examples/compose/plot_digits_pipe.html

https://scikit-learn.org/stable/auto_examples/applications/plot_face_recognition.html

summary¶

  • loading a dataset
  • visualizing data (& low-d representations)
  • applying simple analyses with .fit(X,y)
  • evaluating and comparing model fits (test & training sets, cross-validation)
  • combining several methods ('pipelining')
